WEBVTT

00:00:14.110 --> 00:00:15.840
Huh. Kitasan?

00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:22.790
Kitasan! Whatcha doing?

00:00:23.800 --> 00:00:26.000
Nature-sensei!

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:28.200
This again?!

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:36.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:55.610
Umamusume

00:00:49.270 --> 00:00:55.610
Pretty Derby

00:01:59.530 --> 00:02:03.010
Episode 4
My Own Shine

00:02:00.910 --> 00:02:02.090
You can't win?

00:02:02.090 --> 00:02:03.010
Yeah...

00:02:03.220 --> 00:02:06.600
It's just.. the Osaka Hai was yesterday.

00:02:07.350 --> 00:02:11.290
I'm moving into the senior class,
so wanted to win my first race there.

00:02:11.290 --> 00:02:13.020
Get some real momentum going.

00:02:13.610 --> 00:02:14.680
But then...

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:20.950
I lost by a neck's length.

00:02:20.950 --> 00:02:23.160
Only a neck's? That was pretty close.

00:02:23.160 --> 00:02:25.600
You're right, it was close!

00:02:25.600 --> 00:02:28.420
And at the Arima Kinen, I lost
by three-quarters of a length...

00:02:29.060 --> 00:02:31.880
But I just can't find that missing step.

00:02:32.420 --> 00:02:34.490
Now that I think about it,

00:02:34.490 --> 00:02:37.600
I don't have razor-sharp
acceleration like Dia-chan,

00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:41.890
or explosively powerful
legs like Duramente...

00:02:42.140 --> 00:02:47.180
And the more I think about it,
the more anxious I've been getting!

00:02:48.090 --> 00:02:50.390
W-Well, let's start with calming down.

00:02:50.390 --> 00:02:54.700
I think maybe... I know!
Sweets help at a time like this.

00:02:54.700 --> 00:02:57.030
I'll even treat you.

00:02:57.560 --> 00:02:58.810
Thank you so much...

00:02:58.810 --> 00:03:02.490
Don't worry about it at all.
Order whatever you want today!

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:04.930
Nature-sensei!

00:03:04.930 --> 00:03:06.450
Hold it right there!

00:03:06.450 --> 00:03:08.550
You're not getting away this time!

00:03:09.030 --> 00:03:11.130
She's totes ticked off!

00:03:11.500 --> 00:03:13.750
A
I
R

00:03:12.520 --> 00:03:13.750
M
E
J
I
R
O

00:03:12.520 --> 00:03:13.750
D
A
I
T
A
K
U

00:03:13.750 --> 00:03:17.500
Whoa, whoa, whoa, outta the way, come on!

00:03:29.320 --> 00:03:32.030
You two scared me!

00:03:32.420 --> 00:03:35.290
Sorry, are you all right?
You're not hurt, are you?

00:03:35.290 --> 00:03:36.690
I'm okay!

00:03:36.690 --> 00:03:39.060
I see... that's a relief.

00:03:39.570 --> 00:03:40.810
Come on, you two.

00:03:43.120 --> 00:03:46.990
Are you sure you're okay? Does it hurt anywhere?

00:03:48.020 --> 00:03:51.580
I've always been pretty durable!

00:03:51.580 --> 00:03:53.750
Never get sick or injured.

00:03:54.140 --> 00:03:56.190
Whether it's in the ocean or
in the mountains or on a hill,

00:03:54.420 --> 00:03:55.860
Crabs!

00:03:56.190 --> 00:03:58.860
no matter where I would play,
I never got tired.

00:03:56.760 --> 00:03:58.170
I caught it!

00:03:59.630 --> 00:04:01.260
When I was in grade school,

00:04:01.260 --> 00:04:02.510
Don't be scared...

00:04:01.260 --> 00:04:04.970
I fell from the third floor of the
building and only got a little scrape.

00:04:02.680 --> 00:04:03.930
Kita-chan?

00:04:04.090 --> 00:04:05.340
Kita-chan!

00:04:05.510 --> 00:04:06.760
Kita-chan?!

00:04:08.760 --> 00:04:12.060
Anyway, my point is that I'm pretty
confident in how tough I am.

00:04:14.010 --> 00:04:15.090
Is something up?

00:04:15.090 --> 00:04:19.230
Maybe you could put that toughness
to use in your training.

00:04:19.230 --> 00:04:21.020
I mean, think of it...

00:04:21.020 --> 00:04:24.430
Maybe you can handle the kind of hard
training that other girls can't!

00:04:24.430 --> 00:04:27.370
Maybe working on that
would help you win more?

00:04:28.340 --> 00:04:31.370
I-I'm gonna ask my trainer about it!

00:04:31.370 --> 00:04:32.500
Nope.

00:04:33.620 --> 00:04:35.650
Doesn't matter how tough you are.

00:04:35.650 --> 00:04:38.110
The risk of injury is still too high.

00:04:38.110 --> 00:04:40.000
But... But, but...

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:42.170
I want to get stronger!

00:04:42.170 --> 00:04:44.550
So please, let me trainer harder!

00:04:46.030 --> 00:04:47.370
The answer's still no.

00:04:47.370 --> 00:04:49.050
Trainer-san!

00:04:50.260 --> 00:04:55.560
I mean, if you get injured and can't run
in a race, what'd even be the point?

00:04:57.240 --> 00:05:01.240
Still, I get how you feel about
seeing a chance at getting stronger

00:05:01.240 --> 00:05:04.570
and not wanting to give up on it, too.

00:05:05.390 --> 00:05:06.660
Teio.

00:05:06.660 --> 00:05:07.520
Still, though...

00:05:07.520 --> 00:05:08.870
I feel the same way.

00:05:09.240 --> 00:05:12.140
I think it's wonderful
that you're strict with us

00:05:12.140 --> 00:05:14.730
out of concern for our well-being, Trainer...

00:05:15.310 --> 00:05:19.720
But we run in these races
so that we can win them.

00:05:20.270 --> 00:05:23.050
Suzuka-san... Teio-san...

00:05:25.120 --> 00:05:27.260
Please, Trainer-san!

00:05:30.980 --> 00:05:31.970
Trainer...

00:05:31.970 --> 00:05:33.140
Trainer-san.

00:05:37.950 --> 00:05:40.170
All right, I'll think it over.

00:05:41.420 --> 00:05:43.030
Thank you so much!

00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:44.110
Nice!

00:05:44.110 --> 00:05:44.990
Good luck!

00:05:44.990 --> 00:05:47.050
Yeah! Thank you both!

00:05:45.900 --> 00:05:48.060
I guess I know who to ask...

00:05:47.050 --> 00:05:48.060
I'm gonna work hard!

00:05:48.060 --> 00:05:49.160
I'll be praying for you.

00:06:05.200 --> 00:06:07.970
The edge of your acceleration
is sharper than usual today.

00:06:08.370 --> 00:06:12.290
When I think about the Satsukishou coming up,
I can't help but feel motivated.

00:06:12.610 --> 00:06:15.920
I see... It was the same way for me.

00:06:15.920 --> 00:06:20.180
Although I ended up just adding
fuel to the jinx that horse girls

00:06:20.180 --> 00:06:23.110
from the Satono family can't win G1 races.

00:06:23.110 --> 00:06:24.400
Crown-chan...

00:06:24.400 --> 00:06:28.820
I'm counting on you to make our
family's wish, a first G1 victory, reality!

00:06:33.830 --> 00:06:36.160
Huh. Are you going out, Kita-chan?

00:06:36.160 --> 00:06:38.830
Yeah, I'm going to a training camp tomorrow!

00:06:39.610 --> 00:06:40.580
For how long?

00:06:40.580 --> 00:06:44.840
Snacks
Up to 300 yen
* Bananas don't count
Wake up at 5 AM

00:06:40.580 --> 00:06:44.840
Well, there's a month until the Spring
Tennoushou, so... for about a month.

00:06:47.590 --> 00:06:49.050
S-Sorry, Dia-chan!

00:06:49.050 --> 00:06:51.660
I might not be able to make it to the
Satsukishou to root for you tomorrow!

00:06:51.660 --> 00:06:53.040
W-What am I gonna do?!

00:06:53.040 --> 00:06:55.210
Maybe I can make it back just for that?

00:06:55.210 --> 00:06:57.540
Then again, I'm gonna be
up in the mountains...

00:06:57.540 --> 00:06:59.420
It's okay. I'll win.

00:07:01.930 --> 00:07:04.480
I'll make sure to win.

00:07:05.170 --> 00:07:06.460
Dia-chan...

00:07:06.980 --> 00:07:09.260
So do your best, Kita-chan!

00:07:09.260 --> 00:07:11.410
Yeah... Okay!

00:07:11.690 --> 00:07:16.320
But since I won't be around
for a while... I'll miss you.

00:07:16.970 --> 00:07:17.910
Oh, come on.

00:07:18.490 --> 00:07:20.290
But in that case...

00:07:22.340 --> 00:07:23.110
Here!

00:07:24.530 --> 00:07:25.790
A broach?

00:07:25.790 --> 00:07:28.050
Think of this as me.

00:07:28.050 --> 00:07:29.300
Okay?

00:07:31.150 --> 00:07:33.050
Thanks, Dia-chan!

00:07:33.280 --> 00:07:35.850
It's okay. Let's both do our best!

00:07:35.850 --> 00:07:39.870
Yeah. You take this horseshoe too, Dia-chan!

00:07:39.870 --> 00:07:41.260
That's pretty heavy.

00:07:46.270 --> 00:07:49.830
Not another bite...

00:07:51.660 --> 00:07:55.490
I can't eat anymore...

00:08:05.530 --> 00:08:10.020
No more food for me...

00:08:14.210 --> 00:08:15.680
Good morning.

00:08:29.610 --> 00:08:31.990
You two are up early.

00:08:33.570 --> 00:08:38.630
Trainer-san! Uh, what is this?
What exactly is going on?

00:08:39.340 --> 00:08:41.360
This is your training camp, remember?

00:08:43.240 --> 00:08:46.000
Wait. Then Bourbon-san is...

00:08:46.230 --> 00:08:49.390
She's here as your special coach.

00:08:46.520 --> 00:08:49.840
M
I
H
O

00:08:49.390 --> 00:08:52.360
To be honest, hardcore training
isn't really my area of expertise.

00:08:49.980 --> 00:08:52.840
Training Rocks

00:08:52.360 --> 00:08:55.800
And it wouldn't help to throw something
together on the spot, so...

00:08:56.650 --> 00:08:58.570
You can cry and complain if you like,

00:08:58.570 --> 00:09:00.680
but I've been entrusted with this
and will not be holding back.

00:09:00.990 --> 00:09:02.390
It's a pleasure to be working with you.

00:09:02.390 --> 00:09:04.640
Th-The pleasure's all mine!

00:09:04.880 --> 00:09:08.670
Rice-san is also here to prepare your meals.

00:09:08.670 --> 00:09:10.190
I'm Rice.

00:09:10.490 --> 00:09:12.780
I'll work hard to make sure the food's yummy!

00:09:10.710 --> 00:09:13.320
R
I
C
E

00:09:13.620 --> 00:09:17.070
Things are gonna be tough going
forward, but hang in there, Kitasan!

00:09:17.070 --> 00:09:18.950
R-Right!

00:09:18.950 --> 00:09:20.220
I will!

00:09:18.950 --> 00:09:22.950
Umamusume

00:09:18.950 --> 00:09:22.950
Pretty Derby

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:29.960
Mountain Road Dashes         4 Sets

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:29.960
Giant Tire Pulling Dashes                     10 Sets

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:29.960
Interval Running 1,000m                         10 Sets

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:29.960
Breaking Roof Tiles      100 Pieces

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:29.960
Rock Climbing                 10 Sets

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:29.960
Four sets of mountain road dashes,
10 sets of dashing while pulling giant tires,

00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:32.240
10 sets of 1,000-meter interval runs,

00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:33.960
Training Plan

00:09:32.240 --> 00:09:35.390
100 roof tiles to break,
and 10 sets of rock climbing?

00:09:35.390 --> 00:09:37.510
Your goal for this camp

00:09:37.510 --> 00:09:41.100
is to be able to complete this
training plan within three hours.

00:09:41.100 --> 00:09:42.940
Three hours, huh?

00:09:42.940 --> 00:09:44.880
Is that really possible?

00:09:44.880 --> 00:09:47.030
It'll take double that, initially.

00:09:47.030 --> 00:09:49.480
But theoretically, it's possible.

00:09:49.480 --> 00:09:50.900
Which is why you will do it.

00:09:53.100 --> 00:09:54.530
Now, take your position.

00:09:54.530 --> 00:09:55.650
A-Already?!

00:09:55.650 --> 00:09:56.570
Start!

00:10:08.730 --> 00:10:10.240
You're losing pace.

00:10:10.240 --> 00:10:11.500
R-Right!

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:17.070
I thought this would be just like training
on hills, but the ground is so uneven!

00:10:17.070 --> 00:10:19.890
The slopes being at different angles
makes it even harder to run!

00:10:19.890 --> 00:10:22.440
The stress on my legs is
in a different league!

00:10:31.060 --> 00:10:35.150
Unless I lower my center of gravity and
really exert myself, I'm not getting anywhere.

00:10:35.360 --> 00:10:37.950
Use your entire body.

00:10:37.950 --> 00:10:39.490
R-Right!

00:10:47.750 --> 00:10:49.380
Your form's getting sloppy.

00:10:49.380 --> 00:10:50.500
Right!

00:10:53.500 --> 00:10:54.630
Osu!

00:10:57.130 --> 00:10:58.820
You're losing focus.

00:10:58.820 --> 00:10:59.760
O-Osu!

00:10:59.760 --> 00:11:00.730
Osu!

00:11:12.700 --> 00:11:15.150
Next, I need to reach for...

00:11:15.150 --> 00:11:16.180
Over there?

00:11:16.180 --> 00:11:19.570
But this one would be... hang on, maybe...

00:11:21.570 --> 00:11:24.140
Find your route while maintaining focus.

00:11:24.140 --> 00:11:25.580
You need to decide quickly.

00:11:25.850 --> 00:11:28.080
R-Right!

00:11:32.010 --> 00:11:33.670
Wh-What's my time?

00:11:34.060 --> 00:11:35.330
Six hours.

00:11:35.330 --> 00:11:37.010
Just as expected.

00:11:38.800 --> 00:11:40.350
We've got an entire month left.

00:11:40.350 --> 00:11:42.940
You need to get under
three hours in that time.

00:11:42.940 --> 00:11:43.990
Right!

00:11:46.850 --> 00:11:48.990
For now, let's have something to eat.

00:11:52.490 --> 00:11:54.310
Dinner's ready!

00:11:54.310 --> 00:11:56.310
Please, eat up!

00:11:56.700 --> 00:11:57.920
Thank you!

00:11:57.920 --> 00:11:59.950
There's lots left if you want more.

00:11:59.950 --> 00:12:01.820
Thank you so much!

00:12:01.820 --> 00:12:03.380
So good!

00:12:03.380 --> 00:12:06.740
Once you're done eating, head to the
hot springs and recuperate some.

00:12:06.740 --> 00:12:09.490
There's a hot springs?! Awesome!

00:12:14.870 --> 00:12:16.660
I feel alive again.

00:12:17.430 --> 00:12:18.900
Ow, ow, ow...

00:12:19.810 --> 00:12:22.410
I've never been this exhausted before.

00:12:26.870 --> 00:12:30.160
But I bet once I get past it, I'll be stronger.

00:12:30.720 --> 00:12:33.440
Okay, I'm gonna work hard again tomorrow!

00:13:06.890 --> 00:13:08.430
Mackerel in Miso

00:13:06.890 --> 00:13:08.430
Kabayaki-Style Saury

00:14:15.290 --> 00:14:19.040
You're able to reliably
make your target time now!

00:14:19.290 --> 00:14:20.940
Thank you.

00:14:20.940 --> 00:14:23.770
You've maintained your best weight too,
and you're in perfect condition!

00:14:23.770 --> 00:14:25.800
Your preparations went splendidly!

00:14:25.800 --> 00:14:28.370
Right. All that's left is to win.

00:14:31.620 --> 00:14:33.160
And I will win.

00:14:39.150 --> 00:14:41.320
My body feels heavy for some reason.

00:14:48.090 --> 00:14:50.920
You're losing focus. Steady your breath.

00:14:50.920 --> 00:14:52.160
Osu!

00:14:53.810 --> 00:14:55.410
O... Osu...

00:14:59.800 --> 00:15:03.340
Next is... over here... uh...

00:15:13.800 --> 00:15:15.790
Okay, goodnight.

00:15:15.790 --> 00:15:18.610
Y-Yeah... get plenty of rest, okay?

00:15:23.820 --> 00:15:26.080
Is she seriously gonna be okay?

00:15:26.080 --> 00:15:27.400
What do you mean?

00:15:27.400 --> 00:15:31.090
Her time hasn't improved at
all over the last few days...

00:15:29.070 --> 00:15:35.580
Gonna work hard!!

00:15:29.070 --> 00:15:35.580
Tennoushou!

00:15:31.090 --> 00:15:35.580
And it looks to me like the exhaustion
is taking a toll on her motivation.

00:15:36.170 --> 00:15:37.430
We're just getting started.

00:15:38.330 --> 00:15:42.920
Being able to overcome this is the
actual point of this training.

00:15:43.650 --> 00:15:48.610
It was originally conceived of by Master,
for when I had returned to racing.

00:15:48.610 --> 00:15:49.800
This was all Kuronuma-san's idea?

00:15:50.910 --> 00:15:53.940
A hotly contested competition
is decided by mental strength.

00:15:54.370 --> 00:15:58.890
The ability to pursue victory regardless
of the most extreme circumstances.

00:15:59.810 --> 00:16:04.230
Whether or not she's capable of achieving
this still remains to be seen.

00:16:04.740 --> 00:16:08.400
I was unable to answer to my master's wishes.

00:16:09.050 --> 00:16:14.780
She reminds me of myself, which is
why I hope she will be able to.

00:16:16.900 --> 00:16:18.570
I think I might be done.

00:16:20.620 --> 00:16:23.870
Wait, no, no! I can't start giving in!

00:16:26.240 --> 00:16:29.880
I bet Dia-chan would have gotten
the hang of it in no time.

00:16:33.230 --> 00:16:36.270
Dia-chan... huh?

00:16:36.730 --> 00:16:38.490
Wait, isn't tomorrow...

00:16:42.410 --> 00:16:44.330
There we go.

00:16:45.530 --> 00:16:48.180
Kita-san, Kita-san, I baked some...

00:16:48.180 --> 00:16:49.020
Bread?

00:16:52.480 --> 00:16:54.400
Bourbon-san! Bourbon-san!

00:16:54.680 --> 00:16:56.010
What is it?

00:16:56.410 --> 00:16:59.160
I f-found this in Kita-san's tent!

00:17:00.290 --> 00:17:03.290
I'm going to get energized.

00:17:11.480 --> 00:17:16.780
Come see us again
Iwaki-shi
180km to Nakayama Racecourse

00:17:36.610 --> 00:17:39.120
Satsukishou

00:17:47.580 --> 00:17:50.660
Exiting the final corner...
Satono Diamond is moving up!

00:17:50.660 --> 00:17:52.340
And so is To-Car!

00:17:52.710 --> 00:17:54.010
Dia-chan!

00:17:54.010 --> 00:17:57.250
This is a 310-meter straight:
a direct path to achieving a dream!

00:17:57.250 --> 00:17:58.640
Faucheuse is in the lead!

00:17:58.640 --> 00:18:01.120
On the outside are Satono
Diamond and Jewel Spinel!

00:18:01.120 --> 00:18:02.010
Jewel Spinel!

00:18:02.010 --> 00:18:04.070
Satono Diamond is moving up on the outside!

00:18:04.070 --> 00:18:06.020
Satono Diamond is closing in!

00:18:06.020 --> 00:18:07.310
Dia-chan!

00:18:09.520 --> 00:18:10.960
Faucheuse is still in the lead!

00:18:10.960 --> 00:18:12.000
Then Jewel Spinel!

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:13.000
What about To-Car?!

00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:14.030
Dia-chan?!

00:18:14.860 --> 00:18:17.550
Whoa, and on the outside, it's Divinity!

00:18:17.820 --> 00:18:20.240
Divinity is making a lot of sudden headway!

00:18:20.240 --> 00:18:22.250
To-Car is behind her,
fighting desperately!

00:18:22.250 --> 00:18:23.540
Divinity!

00:18:23.540 --> 00:18:27.040
We're seeing incredible acceleration
create an even bigger gap!

00:18:27.040 --> 00:18:28.870
Divinity crosses the goal!

00:18:27.430 --> 00:18:28.870
Satsukishou

00:18:29.430 --> 00:18:31.880
She managed to pass everyone in an instant!

00:18:31.880 --> 00:18:35.010
Divinity didn't want to
give up the spotlight!

00:18:35.010 --> 00:18:40.170
Her winning time is 1:57.09,
a new race record!

00:18:38.630 --> 00:18:41.300
Nakayama

00:18:39.320 --> 00:18:41.300
Deliberation

00:18:50.310 --> 00:18:51.370
Deliberation

00:18:50.310 --> 00:18:53.060
Nakayama

00:18:51.370 --> 00:18:53.060
Final

00:18:58.570 --> 00:19:00.420
She was doing so well, too.

00:19:00.420 --> 00:19:02.710
Maybe the Satono jinx is real.

00:19:03.160 --> 00:19:04.580
Dia-chan...

00:19:17.960 --> 00:19:19.550
Dia-chan...

00:19:19.940 --> 00:19:22.590
I'll make sure to win.

00:19:23.230 --> 00:19:24.680
Is she gonna be okay?

00:19:25.350 --> 00:19:28.580
Do you have any thoughts
on how the race was called?

00:19:28.990 --> 00:19:30.980
The call was the right one.

00:19:31.210 --> 00:19:34.250
If I had sufficient ability,
it would've been different.

00:19:34.670 --> 00:19:39.110
My ability...
My desire to win wasn't enough.

00:19:39.430 --> 00:19:42.970
There are people in the audience
talking about the Satono jinx.

00:19:43.290 --> 00:19:45.350
Be sure to watch the Japanese Derby.

00:19:48.200 --> 00:19:50.960
My name is Satono Diamond.

00:19:56.210 --> 00:19:59.870
Diamonds are gems that shine
brighter than any other,

00:20:00.250 --> 00:20:03.470
and no matter what they encounter,
they never break.

00:20:49.290 --> 00:20:51.030
I baked some bread.

00:21:03.840 --> 00:21:05.990
You seem re-energized.

00:21:05.990 --> 00:21:06.920
I am!

00:21:08.780 --> 00:21:10.860
Let's resume, then.

00:21:14.970 --> 00:21:17.290
This is it! This is where it really starts!

00:21:22.550 --> 00:21:26.840
Doesn't matter how tired I feel
or how slow the going is!

00:21:26.840 --> 00:21:29.300
I'm not giving up!

00:21:35.060 --> 00:21:38.060
No matter how hard it gets,
I'm only facing forward.

00:21:39.310 --> 00:21:42.880
No matter what the trouble is,
I'll smash past it!

00:21:47.450 --> 00:21:49.780
Next time, I swear...

00:21:49.780 --> 00:21:51.330
Ten seconds left!

00:21:51.740 --> 00:21:53.690
I will make it!

00:21:57.120 --> 00:22:00.630
I'm gonna win!

00:22:16.190 --> 00:22:17.640
You made it over the wall.

00:22:29.320 --> 00:22:31.970
We're going after the Spring Tennoushou!

00:22:31.970 --> 00:22:33.050
Yes!

